rComments: Love this guy. So time efficient and easy to get along with
He sometimes does things the harder way or uses language we don't necessarily know, but he's aware of when we don't understand a concept and will re-state it. It's comfortable to ask him questions.

Dmitri is a strong lecturer, especially given that this was his first time teaching. He is very caring and concerned about his students, going out of his way to be fair and helpful. He gives decent concept explanations and written solutions to difficult problems during lecture. His sense of humour (although quirky and weird) makes classes bearable.

although he's new at teaching, he knows his stuff and he very much cares about his student's concerns. sometimes class can get slow when nobody wants to put their hand up but he's definitely not an intimidating person. his youthful sense of humour keeps the dreadful class more bearable. he's also open to criticism which is good.
